comments: DeRozan (CHI) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Caruso (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the marginal contact initiated by Holiday (MIL) during the driving shot attempt.
Middleton (MIL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) contests Vucevic's (CHI) shot and marginal contact occurs as he inadvertently contacts Vuecvic's foot after he returns to the ground.
Vucevic (CHI) rests a bent arm on Antetokounmpo's (MIL) body, and marginal contact occurs during the post-up.
Caruso (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Holiday's (MIL) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
DiVincenzo (MIL) turns into and delivers contact to DeRozan's (CHI) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) is slightly late to firm up in Caruso's (CHI) path and marginal leg to leg contact occurs as Caruso tries to squeeze through the pick.
During the rebound, Caruso (CHI) and Antetokounmpo (MIL) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal. Caruso and DeRozan (CHI) make clean ball contact to dislodge it from Antetokounmpo.
Dosunmu (CHI) and Matthews (MIL) go to the floor to pursue the loose ball and cleanly tie it up. A jump ball is correctly called.
Holiday (MIL) absorbs the contact from Vucevic (CHI) and avoids any contact with Vucevic's arm during his steal attempts in the post.
DiVincenzo (MIL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
White (CHI) moves into Middleton (MIL) and delivers contact to his body, which affects his SQBR. The foul occurs before the timeout request by the Bucks bench.
Holiday (MIL) maintains a legal guarding position on DeRozan (CHI) during the drive.
Middleton (MIL) extends his leg out into the passing lane and makes contact to deflect the inbounds pass. A kicked ball is correctly called.
White (CHI) releases from DiVincenzo (MIL) to pursue the long rebound and cleanly taps the ball out.
Caruso (CHI) and Holiday (MIL) come together to pursue the loose ball and any contact during the rebound is deemed incidental.
DiVincenzo (MIL) and White (CHI) both go to the ground and make clean ball contact during their pursuit for the loose ball. Any follow-through contact during the rebound is deemed incidental.
